# Final Project — Bio-Inspired AI Audit Complete + Video Demo

**Course:** ITAI 4374 — Neuroscience as a Model for AI Systems
**Instructor:** Professor Patricia McManus
**Student:** Muhammad Umer | Houston City College | Spring 2026

## Overview

This final project delivered the complete Bio-Inspired AI Audit of ChatGPT (GPT-4o), expanding the midterm pilot with two additional module experiments, a Brain vs. AI Scorecard, and a brain-inspired redesign section, plus a video demonstration.

## Modules Covered

- Module 02: Sequential vs. parallel processing
- Module 03: Optical illusions and bistable perception
- Module 04: Within-session and cross-session memory
- Module 06: Emotional framing and response modulation
- Module 07: Selective attention under information overload

## Key Findings

- ChatGPT mimics parallelism through high-speed serial generation
- No perceptual system — cannot experience ambiguity, only describe it
- Context window serves as working memory with no cross-session consolidation
- Emotional framing shifts response tone but not factual content
- Attentional bottleneck effects appear under deliberate information overload

## Deliverables

- Full written audit report
- Brain vs. AI Scorecard
- Video demonstration of all five experiments
